text: William H. Zeliff Jr. (June 12, 1936 â€“ October 18, 2021) was an American Republican politician. He was a member of the U.S. House of Representatives from New Hampshire's 1st congressional district between 1991 to 1997. Zeliff was born in East Orange, New Jersey. Zeliff died on October 18, 2021 from a long-illness in Venice, Florida at the age of 85.Former three-term Republican U.S. Rep.
